de.weltraumschaf.dht.msg

Enum MessageType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MessageType>
      • de.weltraumschaf.dht.msg.MessageType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<MessageType>

    public enum MessageType
extends Enum<MessageType>
    The types of messages. A separated integer value is stored because over Java compilers it is not guaranteed that an enumeration has always the same ordinal value.But we need a reliable native value to serialize over network.
    Author:
    Sven Strittmatter

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      FIND_NODE
      The recipient of the request will return the k nodes in his own buckets that are the closest ones to the requested key.
      FIND_VALUE
      Same as FIND_NODE, but if the recipient of the request has the requested key in its store, it will return the corresponding value.
      PING
      Used to verify that a node is still alive.
      STORE
      Stores a (key value) pair in one node.
      TEXT
      To send arbitrary ASCII text.
